Anti-dilutive potential common shares for the years ended December 31, 2018, 2017 and 2016 include approximately 1
million shares, 1 million shares and 2 million shares, respectively, that could be issued under the Company's outstanding
convertible notes.  Under the treasury stock method, the convertible notes will generally have an anti-dilutive impact on net income
per share if the conversion prices for the convertible notes exceed the Company's average stock price.
